item.title: What the fuck that mean?
item.dc:creator: @NewbieNewty Newty
item.description:
@NewbieNewty wrote:

Renaming/Refactoring has to do with renaming methods/classes in a source file to make them more easily recognizable as to what they do. It is usually only used when talking about clients though, not servers.

An example of renaming could be this:

You have this method that you know paints an image to a screen.

void randomMethod
{
pseudo code
..
}

Because you know what the method does you can now rename it to something more useful, such as:

void paintImage
{
pseudo code
..
}

Hope that helped. :o
